 Mount Everest - the world's highest mountain - may have been born as Asia was squeezed like a tube ofBSE -0.61 % toothpaste after India smashed into the rest of the continent, scientists say.

The unexpectedly prolonged collision led to the formation of the Himalayas and then caused them to grow ever taller, researchers said.

